SQL - beg-SQL 

Files here:

1) SQL Notepad                  - Chronological timeline of T-SQL Musings

2) adricBeginTry                - Update statement using error catch, LEN & REPLACE functions, and UPDATE from JOIN statement

3) adricInsertUsingGUI          - SSMS GUI INTO script

4) adricLatestEnroll            - Select statement using MAX,CASE

5) adricMERGE                   - Merge statement to sync destination from source (update when MATCHED, insert when not)

6) adricManualQ                 - Mass queue up letters for students (user define TALLY table)

7) adricPartitionBy             - Practicing ROW_NUMBER() over Partion By

8) adricUnionSubQuery           - Format T-SQL to spit out insert statements for me

9) adricUnionSubQuery_2         - Wrap insert statements with error checks, ie: ERROR_NUMBER(), ERROR_MESSAGE(), RAISERROR

10) adricUpdateErrorCatch       - T-SQL batch returns results when bit = 0, commits change when bit = 1, error catching

11) complexUpdatev1             - Update statement using BEGIN TRY,CATCH, OBJECT_ID,DROP Temp TABLE, Variable @Bit to test

12) simpleDlrUpPrvntMistakes    - Prevent DML mistake: SELECT shows before/after change, rollsback data, needs manual COMMIT

13) sproc_gatherAUTOMATEDinfo   - User created sproc gathers and presents VIP FAA info quickly for analyst troubleshooting

14) sqlLoop                     - Loop using WHILE, printing 1-10


